elimination of stomach cancer-related deaths. Our results suggest that stomach 
cancer-related mortality rates are still high in Japan and young women are at 
higher risk of stomach cancer-related death relative to young men and that sex 
ratio is stable or slightly decreased over the 40-y period. It is important to 
